post_text:
COVID-19 Preparedness: School Update – 4/15/2020

Dear BASIS DC community,

In line with Mayor Bowser’s announcement, at this time, BASIS Washington, D.C., will remain closed at least through Friday, May 15, 2020.

Our remote learning efforts will continue through this closure. We are extremely grateful to our students, parents, teacher, and staff for their continued dedication to student learning during this difficult time. We appreciate your enthusiasm and patience!

Thank you for your attention to our messages! Please stay healthy and safe!

Sincerely,

Peter Bezanson
CEO, BASIS Educational Ventures

Aaron Kindel
CEO, BASIS.ed

post_text: ExploraVision held an award ceremony for several of our science club members last week. This group of students competed and became 1st in the region. The ExploraVision competition for K-12 students engages the next generation in real world problem solving with a strong emphasis on STEM. Congratulations Dr. T and Dr. Sundberg for coaching this team to a regional victory!

post_text:
Display your school spirit tomorrow and every Friday thereafter by wearing BASIS DC apparel. Apparel is available for purchase at the Front Office (cash or check only). Also, do not forget to purchase the 18/19 Bundle.

The Bundle includes the Swag bag, a 2018/19 shirt, and a magnet for only $30 while this inventory lasts. After September 14th, the Bundle price will increase. Wear a hoodie, sweatpants, t-shirt, or even uniform to show off your school pride, and exude that BASIS DC “Shine.” **mesh bags are not meant for textbooks**

post_text:
Attention parents big news from DC Mayor Mayor Bowser

Kids Ride Free is getting smarter! Beginning October 1, students will no longer be able to use DC One Cards but will need the new Kids Ride Free SmarTrip card to access public transportation.

Get yours early. Distribution Events are happening this weekend in Wards 3 and 6, so make sure to RSVP Today ➡️ kidsridefree.dc.gov.

post_text:
Calling all students, families, teachers and staff! BASIS DC is looking for next year's t-shirt and zip-up hoodie design and we need YOUR help. The winner of the design for the t-shirt and the zip-up hoodie will receive the very first ones!

To enter the Competition please follow the easy steps below by Friday, July 14th:
• Go to Custom Ink's Design Lab.
• Create your design on the t-shirt or zip-up hoodie
• Save Your Design through your email address.
• Share your design with us by sending the design to mary.klein@basised.com

BASIS DC staff and administration will review all submissions and choose three finalists by July 18th. Starting July 19th, the top finalists will be posted on all social media and voting will begin. The t-shirt design and the zip-up hoodie design with the most votes by Friday, July 28th will win!

*All designs need to be appropriate. The t-shirt design can be on the front or back or both and the zip-up hoodie design can only be on the back.
